 # Defer env var injection and validation until pane has an attached client
 
-
+When the extension creates a new background Zellij session, it immediately injects env var exports and validation commands via write-chars. But Zellij silently drops write-chars and dump-screen actions when no client is attached to the session. This means env vars are never set, validation times out, and the first real command fails.
+
+Fix: defer all injection until there's evidence the pane is live. Options:
+1. Wait for an initial prompt_ready signal (requires shell integration already sourced with the FIFO paths somehow set)
+2. Poll with dump-screen until it succeeds (indicates a client attached)
+3. Don't auto-create sessions — require the user to have a session running first
+4. Notify the user to attach, then retry injection on the next tool call
+
+Option 4 is simplest and matches current UX flow. The extension already notifies the user to attach — it just needs to not inject until the pane is actually reachable.
+
